<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<worksheet>
  <title>Review / Extra Practice</title>

  <exercise>
    <introduction>
      <p>You can/should use Sage!</p>
    </introduction>
    <task workspace="1.5in">
      <statement>
        <p>Describe the solution space to the linear system:
  <md>
  \begin{alignedat}{5}
    2x_1 \amp {}-{} \amp x_2 \amp {}{} \amp \amp {}+{} \amp 3x_4 \amp {}={} \amp 6 \\
    x_1 \amp {}{} \amp \amp {}+{} \amp 3x_3 \amp {}-{} \amp x_4 \amp {}={} \amp 6 \\
    2x_1 \amp {}{} \amp \amp {}+{} \amp x_3 \amp {}+{} \amp 3x_4 \amp {}={} \amp 7 \\
  \end{alignedat}
  </md></p>
      </statement>
    </task>
    <task workspace="1.2in">
      <statement>
        <p>Describe the solution space to the vector equation
  <md>
  \left[
    \begin{array}{cccc}
      2 \amp -1 \amp 0 \amp 3 \\
      1 \amp 0 \amp 3 \amp -1 \\
      2 \amp 0 \amp 1 \amp 3 \\
    \end{array}
  \right]
  \xvec = \threevec667.
  </md></p>
      </statement>
    </task>
    <task workspace="1in">
      <statement>
        <p>Suppose that
  <md>
  \vvec_1=\threevec212, \hspace*{24pt}
  \vvec_2=\threevec{-1}00, \hspace*{24pt}
  \vvec_3=\threevec031, \hspace*{24pt}
  \vvec_4=\threevec3{-1}3, \hspace*{24pt}
  \bvec=\threevec667.
  </md>
  Can <m>\bvec</m> be written as a linear combination of <m>\vvec_1</m>,
  <m>\vvec_2</m>, <m>\vvec_3</m>, and <m>\vvec_4</m>?  If so, find one set of
  weights.</p>
      </statement>
    </task>
    <task workspace="1in">
      <statement>
        <p>Is <m>\bvec</m> in <m>\span{\vvec_1,\vvec_2,\vvec_3,\vvec_4}</m>?</p>
      </statement>
    </task>
    <task workspace="1in">
      <statement>
        <p>Are <m>\vvec_1</m>, <m>\vvec_2</m>, <m>\vvec_3</m>, and <m>\vvec_4</m> linearly dependent?  Explain your thinking.</p>
      </statement>
    </task>
    <task workspace="1in">
      <statement>
        <p>Describe <m>\span{\vvec_1,\vvec_2,\vvec_3,\vvec_4}</m>.  Explain your thinking.</p>
      </statement>
    </task>
  </exercise>

  <exercise>
    <introduction>
      <p>Give a condition on the pivots</p>
    </introduction>
    <task workspace="1in">
      <statement>
        <p>[label=(\alph*)]</p>
      </statement>
    </task>
    <task workspace="0.75in">
      <statement>
        <p>of an augmented matrix such that the associated linear system
    is not consistent.</p>
      </statement>
    </task>
    <task workspace="0.75in">
      <statement>
        <p>of an augmented matrix such that the associated linear system
    has a unique solution.</p>
      </statement>
    </task>
    <task workspace="0.75in">
      <statement>
        <p>of a matrix <m>A</m> such that <m>A\xvec=\bvec</m> is
    consistent for any vector <m>\bvec</m>.</p>
      </statement>
    </task>
    <task workspace="0.75in">
      <statement>
        <p>of a <m>10\times10</m> matrix <m>A</m> such that the homogeneous
    equation <m>A\xvec = \zerovec</m> has a unique solution.</p>
      </statement>
    </task>
  </exercise>

  <exercise workspace="1in">
    <statement>
      <p>Explain why the columns of a matrix are linearly dependent if the matrix has a
column without a pivot.</p>
    </statement>
  </exercise>

  <exercise workspace="1in">
    <statement>
      <p>What is the smallest number of vectors that span <m>\real^{1234}</m>?
  Explain your thinking.</p>
    </statement>
  </exercise>

  <exercise workspace="1in">
    <statement>
      <p>Determine if the following matrix is in reduced row echelon
  form.  If not, perform a sequence of row operations to put it in
  reduced row echelon form (without using any computational device).
  Then give a description of the solution space of the associated
  linear system.</p>
      <p><m>\ds
  \left[
    \begin{array}{cccc|c}
      0 \amp 0 \amp 0 \amp 0 \amp 0 \\
      -1 \amp 2 \amp 0 \amp 0 \amp 3 \\
      0 \amp 1 \amp 0 \amp 1 \amp -2 \\
    \end{array}
  \right]
  </m></p>
    </statement>
  </exercise>

  <exercise>
    <introduction>
      <p>Consider the 2-dimensional vectors <m>\vvec</m> and <m>\wvec</m> shown
  below.</p>
      <p>\begin{center}
    \includegraphics{review-fig}
  \end{center}</p>
    </introduction>
    <task workspace="1in">
      <statement>
        <p>Sketch the linear combination <m>a\vvec + b\wvec</m> with weights <m>a=-3</m>
  and <m>b=2</m>.</p>
      </statement>
    </task>
    <task workspace="1in">
      <statement>
        <p>Can the vector <m>\twovec{3}{-3}</m> be written as a linear combination
  of <m>\vvec</m> and <m>\wvec</m>?  If so, how?</p>
      </statement>
    </task>
  </exercise>

  <exercise>
    <introduction>
      <p>Determine whether the following statements are true or false 
  including a justification for your response.</p>
    </introduction>
    <task workspace="1in">
      <statement>
        <p>[label=(\alph*)]</p>
      </statement>
    </task>
    <task workspace="1in">
      <statement>
        <p>If <m>\vvec_1</m>, <m>\vvec_2</m>, <m>\vvec_3</m> and <m>\vvec_4</m> are vectors
    in <m>\real^3</m>, then their span is <m>\real^3</m>.</p>
      </statement>
    </task>
    <task workspace="1.5in">
      <statement>
        <p>Suppose that the span of <m>\vvec_1,\vvec_2,\ldots,\vvec_{27}</m>
    is <m>\real^{27}</m>.  Then every vector in <m>\real^{27}</m> can be written
    as a linear combination of <m>\vvec_1,\vvec_2,\ldots,\vvec_{27}</m>
    is <m>\real^{27}</m> in exactly one way.</p>
      </statement>
    </task>
    <task workspace="1in">
      <statement>
        <p>Is <m>\bvec</m> is a linear combination of the vectors <m>\vvec_1</m>,
    <m>\vvec_2</m>, and <m>\vvec_3</m>, then the equation
    <md>
    \left[
      \begin{array}{ccc}
        \vvec_1 \amp \vvec_2 \amp \vvec_3 \\
      \end{array}
    \right]
    \xvec = \bvec
    </md>
    is consistent.</p>
      </statement>
    </task>
  </exercise>

  <exercise workspace="1in">
    <statement>
      <p>Find the <m>2\times 2</m> matrix that rotates vectors by <m>180^\circ</m>.</p>
    </statement>
  </exercise>

  <exercise>
    <task workspace=".5in">
      <statement>
        <p>If a set of vectors in <m>\real^{19}</m> span <m>\real^{19}</m> what can you say about the number of vectors in the set?</p>
      </statement>
    </task>
    <task workspace=".5in">
      <statement>
        <p>If a set of vectors in <m>\real^{19}</m> are linearly independent what can you say about the number of vectors in the set?</p>
      </statement>
    </task>
  </exercise>

  <exercise>
    <introduction>
      <p>Suppose <m>T: \real^3 \to \real^4</m> is a matrix transformation defined by a matrix <m>A</m>.</p>
    </introduction>
    <task workspace="1in">
      <statement>
        <p>What are the dimensions of A?</p>
      </statement>
    </task>
    <task workspace="1in">
      <statement>
        <p>Suppose 
	<md>T\left(\begin{bmatrix} 1 \\ 0 \\ 0  \end{bmatrix}\right) = \begin{bmatrix} \s1 \\ \s2 \\ \s5  \\ -7 \end{bmatrix} ,\qquad
	T\left(\begin{bmatrix} 0 \\ 1 \\ 0  \end{bmatrix}\right) = \begin{bmatrix} \s 9 \\ \s 4 \\ -2 \\ \s 1 \end{bmatrix}, \qquad \text{ and }\qquad
	T\left(\begin{bmatrix} 0 \\ 0 \\ 1  \end{bmatrix}\right) = \begin{bmatrix} -3 \\ \s 9 \\ \s 4 \\ -2 \end{bmatrix}.</md>
	Find the matrix <m>A</m> that defines the linear transformation.</p>
      </statement>
    </task>
    <task workspace="1in">
      <statement>
        <p>Find <m>T\left( \begin{bmatrix} 2 \\ -1 \\ 3 \end{bmatrix}\right)</m>.</p>
      </statement>
    </task>
  </exercise>

</worksheet>
